Thank you for considering contributing to Servlist! We welcome contributions from the open-source community to improve and enhance our service listing platform. By following these guidelines, you can help make Servelist better for everyone.

How to Contribute
Fork the Repository: Start by forking the Servelist repository on GitHub.

Clone the Repository: Clone your forked repository to your local machine:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/servlist.git
Create a Branch: Create a new branch for your contribution:

git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
Make Changes: Make the necessary changes and improvements to the codebase.

Test Your Changes: Ensure that your changes are thoroughly tested and do not introduce any new issues.

Commit Your Changes: Commit your changes with a clear and concise commit message:

git commit -m "Add your commit message here"
Push to Your Fork: Push your changes to your GitHub fork:

git push origin feature/your-feature-name
Create a Pull Request: Open a pull request (PR) from your branch to the main branch of the original Servelist repository. Be sure to provide a detailed description of your changes in the PR.

Code Style and Guidelines
Follow the existing code style and conventions used in the project.
Write clear and concise comments to explain your code, especially if it's complex or not immediately obvious.
Reporting Issues
If you encounter any issues or bugs while using Servlist, please report them on our GitHub Issue Tracker. Provide detailed information about the issue and steps to reproduce it.

Code of Conduct
Please adhere to our Code of Conduct when participating in the Servlist community. Be respectful and considerate of others, and maintain a positive and inclusive atmosphere.
